            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

		<!-- 04. Future Vision -->
        <div class="content-section">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <span class="section-number">04</span>
            <h2>Future Vision</h2>
          </div>
          <ul class="dash-list">
            <li><strong>Multi-Channel Integration:</strong> Integrate Manse into social media platforms (Facebook, WhatsApp), public displays, and even phone call centers, making it accessible anytime, anywhere.</li>
            <li><strong>Multilingual Support:</strong> Implement support for multiple languages to serve Tampere's diverse and growing international community, promoting inclusivity.</li>
            <li><strong>Data-Driven Governance:</strong> Leverage data analytics from the vast amount of feedback to help city officials gain a holistic understanding of citizens' needs and identify operational weak points for more informed decision-making.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- 05. Reflection & Key Learnings -->
        <div class="content-section">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <span class="section-number">05</span>
            <h2>Reflection & Key Learnings</h2>
          </div>
          <ul class="dash-list">
            <li><strong>The value of user research:</strong> This project reinforced my belief that deep user research is the cornerstone of great design. Without our initial interviews, we might have overlooked the critical emotional needs of "trust" and "transparency."</li>
            <li><strong>The power of iteration:</strong> Moving from a simple Typeform to a refined Figma prototype across three validation rounds allowed us to correct false assumptions early. Each piece of user feedback brought our design closer to a truly user-centered solution.</li>
            <li><strong>Cross‑cultural collaboration:</strong> Working in a multicultural team taught us to communicate more effectively and to approach problems from different perspectives, proving that diverse teams can achieve exceptional results.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Learning Diary (kept – our nicer CTA) -->
        <div class="content-section">
          <div class="section-heading">
            <h2>Learning Diary</h2>
          </div>
          <p>We documented the journey in detail. Explore the full diary:</p>
          <a href="https://luu.notion.site/Project-Diary-ae0eb7ea0a9742de898cabb3de8242ee?pvs=4" target="_blank" class="report-link">View Learning Diary</a>
        </div>
      </section>
